<p><a href="/wiki/Colonel_(United_States)" title="Colonel (United States)">Colonel</a> <b>John (Richard) Boyd</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1927-01-23"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="01-23"><a href="/wiki/January_23" title="January 23">January 23</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1927" title="1927">1927</a></span>–<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1997-03-09"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="03-09"><a href="/wiki/March_9" title="March 9">March 9</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1997" title="1997">1997</a></span>) was a <a href="/wiki/United_States_Air_Force" title="United States Air Force">United States Air Force</a> <a href="/wiki/Fighter_aircraft" title="Fighter aircraft">fighter</a> <a href="/wiki/Aviator" title="Aviator">pilot</a> and <a href="/wiki/Military" title="Military">military</a> <a href="/wiki/Strategy" title="Strategy">strategist</a> of the late 20th century, whose <a href="/wiki/Theory" title="Theory">theories</a> have been highly influential in the military and in <a href="/wiki/Business" title="Business">business</a>.</p>
